    <& /comp/tablebegin, title=>'Style Notes for Sort Names' &>

    Sort Name is the name that will be used when the artist is listed in a 
    list with other artists, so that all the artists that start with <i>The</i>
    will not end up under T. This also applies to artists who have a regular
    names like <i>Eric Clapton</i> but not bands that have
    ficticious names like <i>Cypress Hill</i>.
    <p>
    <center>
    <b>Sort Name Examples:</b><br>
    <table width=75%>
      <tr>
         <th width=50%>
         Name
         </th>
         <th width=50%>
         Sort Name
         </th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
         <td align=center valign=top>
         The Beatles
         </td>
         <td align=center valign=top>
         Beatles, The
         </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
         <td align=center valign=top>
         Eric Clapton 
         </td>
         <td align=center valign=top>
         Clapton, Eric
         </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
         <td align=center valign=top>
         Cypress Hill 
         </td>
         <td align=center valign=top>
         Cypress Hill
         </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
         <td align=center valign=top>
         Bob Marley and the Wailers
         </td>
         <td align=center valign=top>
         Marley, Bob and the Wailers
         </td>
      </tr>
    </table> 
    </center>
    <& /comp/tableend &>
